The paper deals with the design and analysis of coded caching schemes, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of orthogonal arrays and covering arrays, which are topics in combinatorial design and algorithms (cs.SI). The paper also considers the number of users and the efficiency of transmission, which are relevant to networked systems (cs.NI) and computer communication (cs.CC).
